media$description.$t: DEAF Inc's 4th Annual Deaf Winterfest (DWF4) will be happening on March 2, 2013 at Webster Groves Recreation Center in St. Louis, MO. title.$t: MCDHH Deaf Empowerment Symposium: Elijah Buchholz

media$title.$t: MCDHH Deaf Empowerment Symposium: Elijah Buchholz

media$description.$t:
Missouri Commission for the Deaf and Hard of Hearing presented their annual Deaf Empowerment Symposium 2012:

"Changes with Missouri Department of Mental Health" by Elijah Buchholz

About Elijah Buchholz: He has been a mental health counselor for the past 8 years, working with both mentally ill and substance addicted clients, hearing and deaf, impatient and outpatient.  Elijah has conducted numerous trainings for both mental health clinicians and interpreters across Kansas and Missouri.  In addition, Elijah was born to a deaf family and has been interpreting informally most of his life and formally for the past 11 years.

title.$t: MCDHH Deaf Empowerment Symposium: Hollie Spink

media$title.$t: MCDHH Deaf Empowerment Symposium: Hollie Spink

media$description.$t:
Missouri Commission for the Deaf and Hard of Hearing presented their annual Deaf Empowerment Symposium 2012:

"Onward & Upward: Navigating the Unique Obstacles within the Mental Health Field as a Deaf Professional" by Hollie Barnes Spink

About Hollie Barnes Spink: She is a statewide school psychology consultant for the Wisconsin Department of Public Instruction.  She grew up mainstreamed in a deaf/hard of hearing program and was raised using total communication.  Ms. Barnes Spink obtained a Bachelor's degree in Psychology, with an emphasis in Neuropsychology.  She went on to finish her graduate training in Education and Counseling Psychology from University of Missouri.  As a member of the Wisconsin Educational Services Program Deaf and Hard of Hearing Outreach Team, Ms. Barnes Spink provide consultation in mental health, counseling, psychoeducational evaluations, suicide prevention, behavior modification, and many other areas. Lastly she is also a member of the Wisconsin Mental Health Steering Committee, which focuses upon the process of implementing statewide Mental Health services for the deaf and hard of hearing community in Wisconsin.

title.$t: Deaf Winterfest 3

media$title.$t: Deaf Winterfest 3

media$description.$t:
DEAF Inc. present their 3rd annual, Deaf Winterfest (DWF3). It will be held at Webster Groves Recreation Center on March 17, 2011.

At DWF3, deaf, hard of hearing and hearing people get together to celebrate their deafness and culture. There's plenty of social opportunities, broomball tournament, exhibition booths, and VIP dinner. We're loaded with deaf awareness for hearing community to learn about deaf and hard of hearing community. DWF3 raises funds for DEAF Inc.'s deaf and hard of hearing programs. We hope that we see you there!

For more information, go to our website:
http://winterfest.deafinc.org
